abstract: The biggest field of the year is set for next month’s primary debate near Columbus, hosted by CNN and The New York Times.
snippet: The biggest field of the year is set for next month’s primary debate near Columbus, hosted by CNN and The New York Times.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic field is shrinking. But the number of candidates on the debate stage is about to grow.

headline_main: At Least 12 Democratic Candidates to Debate on Single Stage in Ohio, Party Says
headline_print_headline: Democratic Debate to Have At Least 12, on Same Stage

abstract: Ms. Gabbard earned 2 percent support in a new poll in New Hampshire, enough to secure a spot on the stage in Ohio next month.
snippet: Ms. Gabbard earned 2 percent support in a new poll in New Hampshire, enough to secure a spot on the stage in Ohio next month.
lead_paragraph: Representative Tulsi Gabbard of Hawaii became the 12th Democratic presidential candidate to qualify for the October debate after a poll released on Tuesday showed her with 2 percent support in New Hampshire.

abstract: The Democratic National Committee said it would impose slightly higher thresholds to qualify for the November debate.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee said it would impose slightly higher thresholds to qualify for the November debate.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Democratic National Committee said on Monday that it would demand a slight increase in the polling and fund-raising thresholds that presidential candidates must meet in order to qualify for the party’s November primary debate, a move that may once again shrink the field of participating candidates.

abstract: When the speaker of the House thinks it is politically foolhardy.
snippet: When the speaker of the House thinks it is politically foolhardy.
lead_paragraph: To clarify: The House Judiciary Committee has begun an inquiry to determine whether to recommend the impeachment of President Trump. The effort has been underway since March 4, when the committee announced it would look into “the alleged obstruction of justice, public corruption, and other abuses of power” on the part of the president. Last Thursday, committee members passed a resolution setting the parameters for the investigation “to determine whether to recommend articles of impeachment.” On Tuesday, the panel began what its chairman, Representative Jerry Nadler, has said will be an “aggressive series of hearings” to this end.

abstract: Also this week, Kamala Harris releases a long-awaited plan, Elizabeth Warren wants to expand Social Security, and President Trump has a new Republican challenger.
snippet: Also this week, Kamala Harris releases a long-awaited plan, Elizabeth Warren wants to expand Social Security, and President Trump has a new Republican challenger.
lead_paragraph: A slimmed-down Democratic debate dominated this week’s campaign news — but there were other developments, too. Here’s our weekly catch-up on the 2020 election and the Democratic field.

abstract: The Democratic National Committee has announced that the next debate will be held on Oct. 15, with a possible second night on Oct. 16.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee has announced that the next debate will be held on Oct. 15, with a possible second night on Oct. 16.
lead_paragraph: The New York Times and CNN will co-host the next Democratic debate near Columbus, Ohio, on Oct. 15, with the possibility of a second round one night later depending on how many candidates meet the qualifying criteria.
